** Software Engineer - DevOps **

** Intelligence & Cyber International (ICI) **

** Eight Mile Plains, Brisbane **

L3Harris Micreo is a Brisbane based subsidiary of L3Harris and part of our ICI
Division. We provide design, manufacture, integration and sustainment of
advanced electronic warfare components and subsystems using cutting edge
wideband radio frequency and photonic technology. We are a trusted, sovereign
design and production partner to the Australian Department of Defence and an
established exporter to global defence primes.

** The Opportunity **

Join a great team of talented professionals with world-class technical
expertise who take a combined approach to software engineering and enjoy
working together.

We are a company on the move and with forecasted growth of L3Harris Micreo we
are now seeking to hire a dedicated ** DevOps engineer ** to participate in
and support the growing software development team.

Candidates are required to have a good knowledge base of engineering
principles, theories and techniques and a passion for relevant new
technologies. We are mission focused, agile and take innovation seriously.

** Responsibilities **

  * Establishing, maintaining and evolving the development operations infrastructure, including the software engineers’ standard development environment, DevOps services and server infrastructure on both Official: Sensitive and Classified networks. 
  * Work closely with development teams on multiple projects to understand and implement their CI/CD requirements. 
  * Be the first technical point of contact for troubleshooting DevOps issues. 
  * Deploy software to multiple environments from Development through to Production. 
  * Provide technical input throughout the lifecycle of multiple projects. 
  * Reduce time to market for new features and bug fixes by implementing automated continuous delivery pipelines for software artefacts and platforms. 
  * Improve confidence in the change and release process by providing and maintaining frameworks for automated functional and non-functional testing. 
  * Liaise effectively with the IT and Security teams. 

** Essential Requirements **

  * Extensive experience designing, building and maintaining CI/CD infrastructure, automated processes and tools (ideally in several of Typescript/Python/C++/VHDL). 
  * Ability to work independently or as part of a multi-disciplinary team, adhering to development processes 
  * Excellent computer skills 
  * Excellent communication skills in English, both verbal and written 

** Highly Desirable Requirements **

  * An existing NV1 security clearance. 
  * Experience with automated build and test of embedded applications (emulation and/or Hardware-in-the-Loop). 
  * Experience with Jira, Bitbucket, Jenkins, Artifactory. 
  * Experience with Docker. 
  * Experience with Cross-Domain Solutions (CDS). 
  * Experience with static analysis of C++ and python. 
  * Experience with Yocto. 
  * Experience with integration of security requirements into CI/CD pipelines. 
  * Experience with combining classified and unclassified code bases. 

** **

** About us **

L3Harris is dedicated to recruiting and developing diverse, high-performing
talent who are passionate about what they do. Our employees are unified in a
shared dedication to our customers’ mission and quest for professional growth.
L3Harris provides an inclusive, engaging environment designed to empower
employees and promote work-life success. Fundamental to our culture is an
unwavering focus on values, dedication to our communities, and commitment to
excellence in everything we do.

L3Harris Technologies is an agile global aerospace and defence technology
innovator, delivering end-to-end solutions that meet customers’ mission-
critical needs. The company provides advanced defence and commercial
technologies across air, land, sea, space and cyber domains. L3Harris has
approximately $18 billion in annual revenue and 48,000 employees, with
customers in more than 100 countries.

** A few of our employee benefits include: **

  * 5 Weeks annual leave 
  * Flexible working hours and hybrid working where possible 
  * Flexible annual leave (buy & sell up to 2 weeks) 
  * Salary continuance insurance (SCI pays 75% of your base salary and bonus for up to 
  * 2 years) 
  * Discounted private health insurance 
  * Life & Total Permanent Disability Cover 
  * Novated Car Leasing 

